        .info_vertical.animated
          %h1
            Contribute to OpenShift
            %span Origin
          %p We know you've got great ideas for improving OpenShift Origin. So roll up your sleeves and come join us in the community.  
        %i.fa.fa-code.right
        .paddings
          .container.wow.fadeInUp
            .row
              .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-6.col-lg-6
                %h2 Extend OpenShift
                %p You can add new runtimes and frameworks to OpenShift with community cartridges and quickstarts.
                %p
                  The Origin architecture builds upon the flexibility and scalability of Docker and Kubernetes to deliver a powerful new Platform as a Service system.
                %p
                  All contributions are welcome - OpenShift uses the Apache 2 license and does not require any contributor agreement to submit patches. Please open issues for any bugs or problems you encounter, ask questions on the OpenShift IRC channel (#openshift-dev on freenode), or get involved in the 
                  %a{:href => "https://github.com/GoogleCloudPlatform/kubernetes"} Kubernetes 
                  project at the container runtime layer.
                %h2 Take a look at the Trello Board
                %p 
                  The OpenShift project
                  %a{:href => "https://trello.com/b/nlLwlKoz/openshift-origin-roadmap"} roadmap lives on Trello. 
                  Here is a sampling of topics for those who want to get involved with OpenShift 3:
                  %ul
                    %li 
                      %a{:href => "https://trello.com/c/TZPhbN79"} Docker Integration
                  %ul
                    %li 
                      %a{:href => "https://trello.com/c/ja8bbQwy"} Kubernetes Networking
                  %ul
                    %li
                      %a{:href => "https://trello.com/c/3zHeVSla"} Routing and Load Balancing
              .col-xs-12.col-sm-6.col-md-6.col-lg-6
                %h2 Hack on the source code
                %ul
                  %li
                    Get started with the
                    %a{:href => "https://github.com/openshift/origin/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.adoc"} Contributors Guide
                  %li
                    Fork
                    = succeed "." do
                      %a{:href => "https://github.com/openshift/origin"} the repository
                  %li
                    Read the
                    = succeed "." do
                      %a{:href => "http://docs.openshift.org/latest/welcome/index.html"} Origin 3 documentation
                  %li
                    Check out the other repositories we're working on:
                    %ul
                      %li
                        %a{:href => "https://github.com/kubernetes/kubernetes"} Kubernetes 
                      %li
                        %a{:href => "https://github.com/docker/docker"} Docker
                      %li
                        %a{:href => "https://github.com/projectatomic/"} Project Atomic
                %h2 File a bug
                %p
                  Found a bug? Let us know! OpenShift uses a
                  = succeed "." do
                    %a{:href => "https://bugzilla.redhat.com/describecomponents.cgi?product=OpenShift%20Origin"} public Bugzilla instance
                %h2 Talk to us
                %ul
                  %li
                    %a{:href => "http://lists.openshift.redhat.com/openshiftmm/listinfo"} Join the public user or development mailing lists.
                  %li
                    %a{:href => "http://webchat.freenode.net/?randomnick=1&channels=openshift-dev&uio=d4"} Join the #openshift-dev channel on Freenode
      
